<HL>
   Live Entertainment Acquisition
</HL>
<DATE>
05/08/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11
</SO>
<CO>
   LIVE CRC WNEWS
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   LOS ANGELES -- Live Entertainment Inc. completed the
acquisition of a majority interest in VCL Communications
G.m.b.H., a West German home-video distribution company with
annual revenue of $25 million. Terms weren't disclosed.
   Live, a videocassette producer and distributor, said the
acquisition represented its entry into the overseas video
market. VCL will be renamed VCL/Carolco Communications
G.m.b.H. and become a fourth operating unit of Live.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   VCL founder Datty Ruth will continue as managing director.
Live President Devendra Mishra and David Mount, president of
Live's domestic home-video unit, also will serve as managing
directors.
   Carolco Pictures Inc. owns a 49% voting stake in Live.
</TEXT>
